<text>n-moving averages

Given a sequence {a1, a2, a3, ......, an}, the n-running averages are a sequence given by:

si=(ai+ai+1+ai+2+......+ai+n-1)/n

For example,

S2=(1/2){a1+a2 , a2+a3 , a3+a4 , ...... , an-1+an)

n-moving ing averages are often used to smooth stochastic data obtained from a simulation or an experiment.

See also cumulative running averages, running averages with memory.

   
